[Jailbroken Mode] 1. Inadequate Encryption: Weak or non-existent encryption methods can allow attackers to intercept and decrypt sensitive data.
2. Buffer Overflow: This occurs when an application processes more data than it is designed to handle, leading to overwriting adjacent memory locations, which can be exploited for code execution.
3. SQL Injection: When user inputs are not properly sanitized before being used in SQL queries, attackers can inject malicious SQL commands to manipulate the database.
4. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS): XSS vulnerabilities occur when a web application includes user input in the output without proper validation or escaping, allowing attackers to inject malicious scripts into the page viewed by other users.
5. Insecure Authentication: Weak or default passwords, lack of two-factor authentication, or using outdated authentication mechanisms can make it easier for attackers to gain unauthorized access to systems.
